    "These results further confirm the crosstalk between energy and inflammation in BEECs.",
    "Moreover, four of the SMMCs (TIIA, CT, SAA, and SAB) reversed the effect of LPS on ATP and/or inflammatory factors under NEB conditions, thus providing a mechanistic basis for the activity of Salvia miltiorrhiza.",
    "Based on intensive studies investigating blood stasis, inflammatory factors in the blood circulation play important roles in the tissue inflammation process (Marshall, 2001; Levi et al., 2004).",
    "Inflammatory factors released from platelets, erythrocytes and leukocytes can indirectly cause tissue damage, such as edema and exudation (Di Virgilio et al., 2001; Siddall et al., 2017; Iba and Levy, 2018).",
    "Consistent with the former studies, we observed that uterine inflammatory factors in the rat blood stasis model were obviously higher than in control rats."
